data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work without requiring `unsafe` context — you just write:

```csharp
Span<nint> nints = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't fixed at compile time), but you can use `nint.Size` instead. On this 64-bit system, each native int is 8 bytes.
